</TR><TR><TD style=\\\"HEIGHT:4.06mm;WIDTH:0.00mm\\\"></TD><TD COLSPAN=\\\"20\\\"></TD></TR><TR VALIGN=\\\"top\\\"><TD style=\\\"HEIGHT:4.06mm;WIDTH:0.00mm\\\"></TD><TD></TD><TD COLSPAN=\\\"5\\\"><TABLE CELLSPACING=\\\"0\\\" CELLPADDING=\\\"0\\\" LANG=\\\"en-US\\\" style=\\\"\\\"><TR><TD style=\\\"WIDTH:42.67mm;min-width: 42.67mm;HEIGHT:4.06mm;\\\" class=\\\"a24\\\">Notice Text</TD></TR></TABLE></TD><TD ROWSPAN=\\\"2\\\" COLSPAN=\\\"14\\\"></TD></TR><TR><TD style=\\\"HEIGHT:1.78mm;WIDTH:0.00mm\\\"></TD><TD COLSPAN=\\\"6\\\"></TD></TR><TR VALIGN=\\\"top\\\"><TD style=\\\"HEIGHT:6.35mm;WIDTH:0.00mm\\\"></TD><TD></TD><TD COLSPAN=\\\"21\\\"><TABLE CELLSPACING=\\\"0\\\" CELLPADDING=\\\"0\\\" LANG=\\\"en-US\\\" style=\\\"\\\"><TR><TD style=\\\"WIDTH:195.11mm;min-width: 195.11mm;HEIGHT:6.35mm;\\\" class=\\\"a54 r8\\\"><DIV style=\\\"overflow-x:hidden;WIDTH:193.70mm;\\\"><DIV style=\\\"margin-top:10pt;padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:'\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif';font-size:11.0pt;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Columbia Gas Transmission, LLC (TCO) notifies customers of upcoming maintenance activities on Line H&#160;scheduled to begin on Wednesday, April 1, 2026. As a result, the following meters will be reduced to zero total capacity effective Timely Cycle for Gas Day April 1, 2026, and continuing until the work is complete:</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:'\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif';font-size:11.0pt;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">821917 – A&amp;W-Gandee</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:'\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif';font-size:11.0pt;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">840254 – Vandalia</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:'\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif';font-size:11.0pt;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">842446 – Spencer H Line Sales</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:'\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif';font-size:11.0pt;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Based on current scheduled volumes, the anticipated impact to firm service is less than 2,000 Dth/day.&#160;</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:'\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif';font-size:11.0pt;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Additionally, during the first phase of the outage (tentatively scheduled April 1-16, 2026), meter 833237 (behind MLI CNR18) will be required to&#160;physically shut in. Therefore, effective Timely Cycle for Gas Day April 1, 2026, CNR18 will be reduced to zero non-firm.</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:'\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif';font-size:11.0pt;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">TCO encourages customers to monitor the Construction and Maintenance Schedule and the Daily Capacity Posting for any non-firm adjustments related to this maintenance.</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:'\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif';font-size:11.0pt;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Reservation charge credits (RCCs) will be determined per the process set forth in the General Terms and Conditions, Section 38 of TCO’s FERC Gas Tariff (“Tariff”).&#160;However, TCO will only issue RCCs if TCO is unable to schedule or deliver primary firm nominated capacity as a result of the outage.&#160;In the event RCCs are issued as set forth in the Tariff, shippers will receive RCCs based on its 7-day average usage quantity less any scheduled quantities on the contract. By means of this notice, TCO is establishing which specific Gas Days will be included when determining a shipper’s 7-day average usage quantity pursuant to the provisions in the Tariff.</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:'\\\"calibri\\\",sans-serif';font-size:11.0pt;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Please contact your Customer Services Representative with any questions.</span></DIV></DIV></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV></TD><TD WIDTH=\\\"100%\\\" HEIGHT=\\\"0\\\"></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH=\\\"0\\\" HEIGHT=\\\"100%\\\"></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV></DIV></body></html>\"},\"startTime\":\"2026-04-20T17:14:14.8702246Z\",\"endTime\":\"2026-04-20T17:14:14.9392901Z\",\"trackingId\":\"5a17da68-bc3b-4c33-aa08-3515b93c695b\",\"clientTrackingId\":\"08584249018052146792210398495CU00\",\"code\":\"OK\",\"status\":\"Succeeded\"},{\"name\":\"Call_Foundry_Extraction\",\"inputs\":{\"uri\":\"https://cog-dte-noticeapp-eus2-mx01.cognitiveservices.azure.com//openai/deployments/gpt-5.2/chat/completions?api-version=2024-02-01\",\"method\":\"POST\",\"body\":{\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"system\",\"content\":\"You are a structured data extraction assistant. Extract information from HTML documents and return only valid JSON. Be precise and thorough.\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Extract these fields from the HTML notice as JSON:\\n- title: The main notice title/subject\\n- noticeType: Type of notice (Maintenance, Capacity Constraint, Force Majeure, etc.)\\n- status: Initiate, Supersede, or Cancel\\n- postedDate: When notice was posted (ISO 8601)\\n- effectiveDate: When notice takes effect (ISO 8601)\\n- endDate: When notice expires (ISO 8601, null if none)\\n- description: Main content/body of the notice (cleaned text, not HTML)\\n- affectedLocations: List of affected locations/meters if mentioned\\n- responseRequired: true if response is required, false otherwise\\n\\nReturn ONLY valid JSON, no markdown or explanation.\\n\\nHTML Content:\\n<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \\\"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN\\\" >\\n<html><head><title>NoticesSubreport</title><META http-equiv=\\\"Content-Type\\\" content=\\\"text/html; charset=utf-8\\\"/><META http-equiv=\\\"Content-Style-Type\\\" content=\\\"text/css\\\"/><META http-equiv=\\\"Content-Script-Type\\\" content=\\\